This is an excellent recording app and the only one I've found that has full functionality on Android 9 (with root). I used to use another app, Call Recorder Pro, but it stopped working when Google shut the API for accessing call audio in Android 8. I'm glad I found this app's Magisk module while randomly browsing modules in the main repo, as I feel that recording calls is essential in fighting corporate greed. With all my calls recorded, if a customer service representative promises something and fails to deliver, I can play back the recording to their supervisor and push that promise through.

What can I say, this call recorder works, and it works well! It's been hard finding one that'll work on Android 9 even ones that claim to work but require root, generally didn't work as you'd expect. And if you do have a problem, just email the developer and they'll soon fix any issues.

Great app but not quite five stars.  It's a really reliable app, but it's missing two vital features.  1. Recording jog function: I frequently transcribe my recordings and having a configurable button that rewinds a few seconds (eg 5 or 10 seconds) would save countless minutes trying to so so manually in the timeline.  Using the app on a small smartphone screen means it's easy to overshoot timeline rewinding.   Plenty of other recording apps have this feature - why can't Call Recorder?  2. 180 degree app rotation.  I'm often required to transcribe right when my phone needs charging. Although the app can  rotate 90 degrees to landscape (horizontal), it would be nice if it could rotate 180 degrees.  This is because my phone, like many, has its charging cable port on the bottom of the phone. As I frequently pick up my phone whilst transcribing recordings, the cable gets in the way....unless you could turn the app upside down and have the cable at the top of the phone.
